{"name":"The Brand of Greed","type":"item","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-sealed-red-yellow.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"Bardolf Greed has granted you The Brand of Greed, a special pass that marks you as one of his trusted associates. This ornate document bears Bardolf's personal seal and signature, and it is recognized throughout Whitehaven as a symbol of ultimate authority. With The Brand, you get free access to any place in the city—factories, the slaughterhouse, the mine, even Greed's mansion—without anyone being able to object to your entrance. Guards, workers, and officials must comply immediately or face Bardolf's wrath. Additionally, you get 1 Additional Success when you exploit the Brand's importance and Bardolf's backing against any city dweller. Threaten them with Bardolf's displeasure, demand cooperation in his name, or leverage his resources—the Brand makes it clear you speak with his voice. However, carrying The Brand also marks you as an enemy to the Pig Heads and workers' rebellion. Arthur, Frank, and Clarence will see you as Bardolf's agent and tool of oppression.","somaCost":0,"requirement":"Gain the trust and respect of Bardolf Greed by demonstrating cunning, ability, and willingness to put productivity and profit above workers' lives.","scenario":"The City of Pigs","notes":"This Gift represents siding with industrial tyranny over workers' rebellion. Bardolf only trusts those who demonstrate his own values: ruthlessness, cunning, and prioritizing property over people. The free access to all locations is incredibly powerful for investigation but comes with a moral cost. The +1 Additional Success when exploiting the Brand against city dwellers makes social encounters easier but reinforces your position as Bardolf's enforcer. The Browne brothers will react with hostility—any attempt to negotiate with them while carrying The Brand receives penalties. This Gift creates fascinating moral dilemmas: use Bardolf's authority to stop the Pig Heads' violence, or recognize that the workers have legitimate grievances? The Brand can also be used cleverly—forge documents in Bardolf's name, access restricted areas to gather evidence against him, or even frame him for crimes. Storytellers should emphasize how workers react to seeing The Brand: fear, resentment, and disgust. This Gift is most useful for Hunters who want to infiltrate Bardolf's organization or who genuinely believe the Pig Heads' revolution will cause more harm than good."},"_id":"2ca475e964a0721d"}
{"name":"The Meat of The God Under the Mine","type":"item","img":"icons/consumables/meat/steak-raw-red.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You possess a piece of the divine flesh torn from The God Under the Mine. The meat regenerates slowly, allowing repeated use. Once per Scene, you can consume a portion of the flesh to temporarily gain supernatural power. When you do, immediately heal 1 Wound and gain 1 Additional Success on all physical actions you take for the rest of that Scene (attacks, climbing, running, lifting, swimming, etc.). The power courses through your body, making you stronger, faster, and more resilient. However, you must wait an entire Scene for the remaining flesh to regenerate before you can use this Gift again. **WARNING:** If you use this Gift in 2 consecutive Scenes without waiting for regeneration, the flesh is completely consumed and you permanently lose this Gift. The temptation to rely on divine power comes with a cost.","somaCost":0,"requirement":"Obtain a piece of the flesh of The God Under the Mine—either by visiting the slaughterhouse and finding Frank's stash, or by defeating one of the Spawn of the God and harvesting its meat.","scenario":"The City of Pigs","notes":"This is a powerful but dangerous Gift that embodies the central temptation of the scenario. The meat grants genuine power (+1 Additional Success on ALL physical actions for entire Scene, plus heal 1 Wound), making it extremely useful in combat. The regeneration mechanic (must wait full Scene between uses) encourages strategic timing. The permanent loss condition (use 2 consecutive Scenes = Gift consumed) creates dramatic tension—do you risk losing the Gift to survive a dire situation? This mirrors Arthur Browne's own corruption: he started using the God's flesh out of desperation but became addicted to its power. Hunters who use this Gift frequently may begin to show physical changes (pig-like features) at the Storyteller's discretion, foreshadowing transformation into Pig Heads. The Gift doesn't require Soma, making it accessible but also tempting to overuse. Frank Browne has been secretly mixing this flesh with beef to create Pig Heads—Hunters with this Gift understand firsthand why workers would transform."},"_id":"9cdab200c546ad9e"}
{"name":"There Is No House That Can Stop Me","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/air/wind-tornado-wall-blue.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"**SPECIAL GIFT FOR GAROU THE OLD WOLF ONLY.** Those damned pigs get on your nerves and you can't stand them running away from your wrath. Your primal fury awakens when facing the Browne brothers, channeling the rage of the Big Bad Wolf who could blow down any house. You get 2 Additional Successes when you take action to destroy or overcome any environmental obstacle that stands between you and one of the three Browne brothers who has used their Gang Leader Gift (Arthur, Frank, or Clarence in mutated pig form). This includes: blowing down doors with supernatural breath, smashing through walls, demolishing barricades, collapsing tunnels to create shortcuts, breaking through floors or ceilings, destroying steam engines or machinery used as obstacles, or even collapsing entire buildings if they're hiding inside. Your rage makes the impossible possible—no structure can protect them from you. However, you hate to lose to them. If you have to leave or flee from a Scene without eliminating one of the three pig brothers, your shame and fury cause you to lose 1 Soma immediately. You are the Big Bad Wolf, and pigs cannot escape you.","somaCost":0,"requirement":"Clash with one of the Browne brothers (Arthur, Frank, or Clarence) who has activated their Gang Leader Gift to transform into a monstrous pig form.","scenario":"The City of Pigs","notes":"This Gift is exclusive to Garou the Old Wolf, connecting directly to his fairy tale origin as the Big Bad Wolf from The Three Little Pigs. The +2 Additional Successes (instead of the usual +1) for destroying obstacles makes Garou incredibly effective at pursuing the brothers—no house of straw, sticks, or even brick can stop him. The Gift specifically triggers when the brothers use Gang Leader to mutate, emphasizing that Garou is hunting monsters, not men. The environmental destruction is broad: anything physical between Garou and his prey can be demolished with supernatural ease. This creates cinematic moments: Garou huffing and puffing to collapse mine tunnels, smashing through factory walls, or even collapsing Arthur's cave by destroying support pillars. The penalty (lose 1 Soma if you flee without eliminating a brother) reflects Garou's pride and hunting instinct—retreat is shameful for the Wolf. This can force difficult decisions: pursue vengeance and lose Soma, or tactically withdraw? Storytellers should emphasize Garou's wolf nature when this Gift activates: glowing eyes, lupine features becoming more pronounced, and supernatural breath that can shatter stone. The Three Little Pigs fairy tale structure is reversed—now the Wolf can actually blow down the houses, making the pigs the prey."},"_id":"c957a925064c3328"}